Lanka Orix Leasing Rises After Getting Holding Company Status

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e
-- 
2011-04-08T05:42:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/lanka-orix-leasing-rises-after-getting-holding-company-status.html
Lanka Orix Leasing Plc rose the most
in almost three months in Colombo trading after saying it got
the central bank’s approval to function as the holding company
of a group which has expanded into tourism, agriculture,
technology, construction and renewable energy.  Colombo-based Lanka Orix rose as much as 9.3 percent and
was trading 7.5 percent higher at 125.90 rupees at 11:05 a.m.
local time. Lanka Orix said the new structure would help the
group “reach a phase of exponential growth in the coming
years.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in Colombo at 
 anushao@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
